div.p:
Therefore, we should begin in New York or elsewhere, talking with the Russians
                    and, if possible, with the Egyptians and others about the terms of a settlement: 

—Eilat open to oil;

—observers on both sides of the line;

—a Soviet commitment to work with us to damp down the arms
                            race;

—a turn in the road on refugees;

—a Middle East development bank that would bring the Iranians and
                            Turks into the diplomacy of the area; etc.
